<TITLE> Crackdown starts now: AL </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka , April 4 (bdnews24.com)Awami League has said a crackdown against ongoing campus violence "starts now". AL spokesperson Syed Ashraful Islam told reporters Saturday the government was cracking down countrywide on all violence by "students or in the name of students". "The government has instructed law enforcing agencies to take action against violence by students leaders, members or activists, or anyone perpetrating violence, extortion, terrorism in the guise of students," he said. "The action starts now," said Ashraf, after a meeting of the party presidium chaired by AL chief Sheikh Hasina. Ashraf had earlier in the day warned of the sternest measures, when he was questioned about ongoing campus violence. "The government is pledge-bound to take stern lawful action against all extortionists, terrorists and corrupt," the local government minister told reporters, who pressed him to comment on the recent bouts of violence by the ruling party-backed BCL. bd
